  <front>
   <head>An EPIGRAM. On the Reverend Mr. LAURENCE ECHARD's, and Bishop GILBERT BURNET's Histories.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">GIL'S history appears to me</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Political anatomy,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A case of skeletons well done,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And malefactors every one.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">His sharp and strong incision pen</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Historically cuts up men,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And does with lucid skill impart</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Their inward ails of head and heart.</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">LAURENCE proceeds another way,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And well-dress'd figures doth display:</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">His characters are all in flesh,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Their hands are fair, their faces fresh;</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And from his sweet'ning art derive</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A better scent than when alive.</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">He wax-work made to please the sons,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Whose fathers were GIL'S skeletons.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
